
@startuml

' Class Definitions

class Song {
  -title: String
  -year: Integer
  -length: Integer
  -genre: String
  -trackNumber: Integer
}

class Artist {
  -name: String
  -dateOfBirth: Date
  -websiteUrl: String
}

class User {
  -id: Integer
  -name: String
  -address: String
}

class RegularUser {
  -canBuySingles: Boolean
  -canBuyAlbums: Boolean
}

class BusinessUser {
  -vatNumber: String
  -canUploadSongs: Boolean
}

class Album {
  -title: String
  -trackList: List<Song>
}

class Single {
  -title: String
}

class Hit {
  -title: String
  -trackNumber: Integer
}

' Associations and Relationships

Song "1" -- "1" Artist : belongsTo
Artist "1" -- "*" Song : has

User "1" -- "*" Song : owns (as BusinessUser)
User "1" -- "*" Album : owns (as BusinessUser)

User "1" -- "*" Single : buys (as RegularUser)
User "1" -- "*" Album : buys (as RegularUser)

BusinessUser "1" -- "*" Song : uploads
BusinessUser "1" -- "*" Album : creates

Album "1" -- "*" Hit : contains
Hit "1" -- "1" Song : isA

RegularUser <|-- User
BusinessUser <|-- User

Single <|-- Song
Hit <|-- Song

@enduml

---

### 📌 Explanation of Key Elements:

- **Song** contains title, year, length, genre, and track number. It can be either a **Single** or a **Hit**.
- **Artist** has name, date of birth, and a website URL. Each artist is uniquely identified by their name.
- **User** is the base class with `id`, `name`, and `address`. Two subclasses:
  - **RegularUser**: Can buy singles and albums.
  - **BusinessUser**: Can upload songs and create albums; also has a VAT number.
- **Album** consists of multiple **Hits**, each with a track number.
- **Single** is a type of song that can be bought directly.
- **Hit** is a type of song that appears in an album.

